f=Cybersecurity/warden/operational/commands/warden-commands.md · h1:warden — Command Triggers=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · h1:warden — Command Triggers=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:warden — Command Triggers=\| "security policy," "control framework," "map us to NIST/ISO/SOC 2," "ISMS," "control gap" \| security-policy-framework \| /warden-isms \| · h1:warden — Command Triggers=\| "risk," "risk register," "score this risk," "accept the risk," "top risks," "prioritize security" \| risk-register \| /warden-risk \| · h1:warden — Command Triggers=\| "vendor security," "third-party risk," "assess this SaaS," "DPA," "supply chain" \| third-party-risk \| /warden-vendor \| · h1:warden — Command Triggers=\| "exception," "waiver," "we can't meet control X," "temporary exception" \| security-exception-process \| /warden-exception \| · h2:Precedence=gap/finding/incident/vendor issue lands **risk-register** it's spine; skills feed it. Any **risk acceptance** above threshold board (Governance); warden recommends, never self-accepts material risk. Any **privileged execution** (provisioning, containment, remediation) operator; warden holds keys (the security-inversion). Material policy changes anneal board (Fleet Charter Rail 3); senior charters unchanged.